7. User Scenarios\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sb240\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Incoming Call:
\f0\b0  The user answers a call on their phone. The phone transmits audio to the Pi via Bluetooth. The Pi routes the audio to the user's wired earpiece and starts a recording script.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Recording Session:
\f0\b0  The user speaks into a high-quality wired lavalier mic. This audio is sent back to the phone so the caller can hear them, and it is simultaneously recorded to the SD card.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f1\b {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}End of Call:
\f0\b0  The script detects the Bluetooth disconnect and closes the WAV file.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Auto-Offload:
\f0\b0  When the user returns to their home/office, the Pi detects the Wi-Fi. It pushes the WAV file to the desktop computer, which then runs Whisper to produce a text summary for the user's CRM/workflow.\
